title: Led Zeppelin - 1975.02.10 Landover, Maryland
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1975.02.10 Landover, Maryland   

Led Zeppelin
February 10th, 1975
Capital Centre, Landover, Maryland, USA
Ultra Violent Killer Droog, 6cd by Empress Valley
Source: soundboard recording (#EVSD 919~921)

Source: 
Almost complete excellent soundboard recording.

Details: 
The recording is a very good balanced professional board tape.

Tracklist: 

Disc 1
01.Introduction
02.Rock And Roll
03.Sick Again
04.Over The Hills And Far Away
05.In My Time Of Dying
06.The Song Remains The Same
07.The Rain Song 
08.Kashmir

Disc 2 
01.No Quarter
02.Trampled Underfoot
03.Moby Dick

Disc 3

01.Dazed And Confused
02.Stairway To Heaven
03.Whole Lotta Love
04.Black Dog
05.Heartbreaker

Comments:
This sounds excellent! It sounds natural and not too processed. 
Amazingly, the guy at the mixing board managed to get the levels 
right before Rock and Roll instead of during.
The bombastic renditions of Dazed And Confused and Moby Dick, 
when Bonham throws in a couple of rhythm exercises known from 
basic structure of Whole Lotta Love ... played later as an 
usual encore making this show worth listening!
